The paper discusses explainability techniques for Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs), which are commonly used in machine learning tasks such as image classification, natural language processing, and chemistry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
